1. Tcs.m4a
1.	How do you ensure that Jenkins is able to connect to Kubernetes and deploy?
2.	How do you set up the authentication between Jenkins and Kubernetes?
3.	Have you set up any pipeline that is connecting to Kubernetes from Jenkins?
4.	In Kubernetes, if container memory utilization and CPU are very high, what would you do to ensure the application in the container operates properly?
5.	Have you done Horizontal Pod Autoscaling (HPA)? What steps are needed to perform it?
6.	What parameters do you typically specify for autoscaling to work?
7.	Apart from HPA, is there any other way of manual autoscaling you are familiar with?
8.	In Kubernetes, you have two pods for a microservice application: order service and product service. Order service needs to call product service internally. How do you invoke one container service from another?
9.	How do you actually call a service API in container A from container B?
10.	You have an application running in a container inside a Kubernetes cluster that needs to read/write files to an S3 bucket. What would you do so that the code in the container can connect to S3 and read/write files?
11.	How do you ensure the running container is actually using/assuming that IAM role?
12.	Same scenario but the code is running on an EC2 instance with an S3 bucket having 10 folders; you must allow read/write only to one folder. How would you do it?
13.	How would you configure the permissions/policy so that only one folder can be read or written and others cannot?

